Test: Definition List Layout

        /* Reset for consistency */
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { 
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; 
            font-size: 16px; 
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 700px;
        }

        /* Typography */
        h3 {
            font-size: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        /* Definition list styles */
        dl {
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        dt {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }

        dt:first-child {
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        dd {
            margin-left: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            color: #555;
        }

        /* Code in definitions */
        code {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 14px;
            background-color: #f3f4f6;
            padding: 2px 4px;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }



    API Definitions
    The following definitions explain key terms used in the API:


        Authentication
        The process of verifying user credentials before granting access to protected resources.

        Bearer Token
        A security token included in the Authorization header of HTTP requests.
        Format: Authorization: Bearer <token>

        Rate Limiting
        A mechanism that controls the number of requests a client can make within a specified time window.

        Webhook
        An HTTP callback that delivers real-time data to other applications when specific events occur.
        Commonly used for notifications and data synchronization.


    These definitions help establish a common vocabulary for API documentation.



